body.description: The Baby Jogger Car Seat Adapters let you quickly and easily turn your stroller into a customized travel system. Use these adapters to attach your Maxi-Cosi or Cybex infant car seat to your Baby Jogger City Select or City Select LUX stroller. You can even fold the stroller while the adapters are still attached, giving you a more versatile travel system.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: About Baby Jogger Baby Jogger strollers are designed by parents, with parents in mind. Since 1984, the company has been inspired by children and the potential to create ingenious solutions for everyday problems. That means helping parents and their children be more places and see more things. From the City Mini line and Summit X3 to the City Select, Baby Jogger offers a stroller for every terrain and every need. So parents and children can easily live active lives everyday. Maxi Cosi Infant Car Seat Adapter The Car Seat Adapter is the easiest way to turn your stroller into a customized travel system. Attaching your car seat to a Baby Jogger stroller has never been easier. You can even fold the stroller with the brackets attached, giving you the most versatile travel system available. Turns stroller into a travel system Folds with the brackets attached Easy to attach infant car seat to stroller

Create Your Own Travel System Create your own Baby Jogger City Select, City Select Lux or City Premier travel system by securely attaching your infant car seat to the stroller. Works with Cybex Aton, Aton 3S, or Aton Q infant car seats. Works with Maxi Cosi Mico AP, Mico Max 30, Pebble, Cabrio Fix, Pebble Plus, or Nuna Pipa infant car seats. Attaches directly to the stroller, no support bars needed. No tools are required for this simple, easy installation process. The stroller even folds with the adapter brackets attached!
Accessorize for Convenience Convenience accessories, like the shopping tote, help make your parenting journey easier!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 21, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fits Clek Liing infant car seat perfectly
reviews.reviewText: This is the recommended adapter to fit the clek liing infant car seat and I’m glad to say it fit and worked for us! Though intended for the mix cosi it works perfectly with the liing. Pretty dang pricey for two pieces of plastic though. Also the webbing seems to have an unknown purpose other than getting in the way of the brake lever. I presume if the mounts to the stroller broke they would provide some safety from catastrophic ground hitting failure. Otherwise it’s great!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect stroller that fit all my needs
reviews.reviewText: After much debate on what stroller to purchase after having our first baby, we decided to go with the baby jogger city select lux, and I am so glad we did. It’s a great stroller with so many great features. The storage basket holds so much, I fit a full Trader Joe’s shopping trip under there!! There are accessories (to purchase separately) to add on that make it the perfect stroller for me. With our new baby we have the Nuna Pipa car seat that is compatible with adaptors and we added the baby jogger parent console so there is a perfect place for my mommy essentials that are easy to access. The console does stay on fine when the stroller collapses, but you’ll want to remove anything that could fall out or get crushed when doing so. Another one of the main reasons I purchased this stroller was that it can convert to a double stroller if we have more children, which is a huge bonus for me. We won’t need to upgrade our stroller since it has the ability to add an additional seat! We haven’t used this stroller with the toddler seat yet since my son is still a baby.A few things to note: it is a pretty big stroller since it does have the ability to convert to a double stroller. It’s a bit long too but you get used to it and it’s really easy to maneuver. I’m 5’4” and I feel like the hight of the handle bars on the stroller is just the right height for me. Anyone that is shorter and this stroller might be too tall for you. But definitely go to a retailer that carries this so you can test it out of possible. If you’re tall, the handle bar can easily be adjusted for you. There is a tab on top of the handle bar that adjusts for you.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 22, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works well with Nuna Pipa and standard Baby Jogger City Select
reviews.reviewText: I have a 2016 Baby Jogger City Select tandem double stroller (standard version). I previously had a 2016 Nuna Pipa that I attached with a different adapter, but that car seat was damaged, so I just replaced it for my newest baby with a Nuna Pipa manufactured in 12/2019 (Standard Pipa, not a Lite), which unfortunately requires a different adapter. This adapter works great on the top slot, closest to the handle. The seat attaches and detaches easily. I have NO idea what the red tab is for. The handlebar strap strikes me as the equivalent of a back-up parachute. I personally don't think it's critical, but I'll generally use it because, despite being 5'2", I often fully extend the handlebar anyway to leave room in front of the Pipa for my Diono storage attachment for cups and phone.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Does the trick, but pricey
reviews.reviewText: We have a nuna car seat and a babyjogger stroller, this was the necessary piece to allow them to connect. It does the job, installation was simple. This was not a prime item so I had to pay for shipping and it took a bit longer than usual, but we are happy to have a functioning stroller setup now.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It’s complicated, but it works.
reviews.reviewText: So after MUCH searching and finding very little information, I knew it was important to leave a review. I have the Maxi Cosi Mico Max 30 infant seat and the City Select Lux stroller. I struggled with these adapters for hours!! The LEFT adapter goes on the left when FACING the stroller from the front, not like if you were pushing it. I struggled because the stroller will allow you to insert them incorrectly, but then the car seat will not attach. So again, each adapter is indicated as left and right and the correct insert is when you are facing the front of the stroller. Once I did that, it was EASY. The car seat clicks right in. To release, you press the two little gray tabs on the left and right side of the car seat. After speaking with somebody who sells the adapters, NO the tethers do not tighten.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 20, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works great for Nuna Pipa
reviews.reviewText: This works great for my Nuna Pipa and Baby Jogger City Select Double stroller. It takes a bit more effort to place the car seat onto the stroller than when using the nuna ring adapter with my other stroller, but I needed the double stroller and this helped fit the bill! Quick tip: To remove the Pipa, you need to press the two top buttons at the same time and wiggle…it’s not smooth…but it works!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nuna Pipa Lite LX
reviews.reviewText: Read a lot of reviews that stated that the Pipa Lite models didn’t work with these adapters, still I decided to take a gamble, after messing with it for a few minutes I noticed that when placing the Right adapter on the Left side of the stroller and vice versa on the other adapter it worked perfectly. If you place the adapter on the sides that they are labeled for you can only back face the car seat, hope this helps!
